title: Musheramore
text:
Musheramore () is a 644 m (2,113 ft) <a href="mountain">mountain</a> in <a href="County%20Cork">County Cork</a>, <a href="Republic%20of%20Ireland">Ireland</a>. It is the highest of the <a href="Boggeragh%20Mountains">Boggeragh Mountains</a>.
There are two <a href="holy%20well">holy well</a>s on the mountain: one at the summit, for sick animals, and one on its northern slopes, for humans. The later is a place of worship and it's called <a href="St.%20John%27s%20Well">St. John's Well</a>.
